Package: seqvisr
Title: Biological Sequence Visualization Functions in R
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person(given = "Venket",
           family = "Raghavan",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "vraghvragh@mailfence.com")
Description: Enables visualization of biological sequences (and manipulation thereof) in R. It currently comprises of a single function msavisr that can be used to visualize multiple sequence alignments. Additional functions (and functionality) to be added in the future.
Imports: viridis, magrittr, stringr, dplyr, tidyr, ggplot2, grDevices
BugReports: https://github.com/vragh/seqvisr/issues
URL: https://github.com/vragh/seqvisr
License: GPL-3 + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
